              "annotations": [],
              "text": "To solve \\( 17 \\times 19 \\), we can use distributive property to simplify the calculation step by step.\n\n### Step 1: Break down \\( 19 \\) into two simpler numbers\nWe can break \\( 19 \\) into \\( 20 - 1 \\). This helps avoid directly multiplying the numbers and makes calculations simpler.\n\nSo,\n\\[\n17 \\times 19 = 17 \\times (20 - 1)\n\\]\n\n### Step 2: Apply distributive property\nThe distributive property states:\n\\[\na \\times (b - c) = (a \\times b) - (a \\times c)\n\\]\n\nApplying this to our equation:\n\\[\n17 \\times 19 = (17 \\times 20) - (17 \\times 1)\n\\]\n\n### Step 3: Calculate each term\n1. \\( 17 \\times 20 = 340 \\)  \n   We get this by multiplying \\( 17 \\) by \\( 2 \\) to get \\( 34 \\), then adding a \\( 0 \\) to account for multiplying by \\( 10 \\).\n2. \\( 17 \\times 1 = 17 \\).\n\n### Step 4: Subtract the results\nNow subtract \\( 17 \\) from \\( 340 \\):\n\\[\n340 - 17 = 323\n\\]\n\n---\n\n### Final Answer:\n\\[\n\\boxed{323}\n\\]",
